Vice President Mike Pence delivered remarks at the Indianapolis Marriott Downtown, expressing gratitude to the Indianapolis Ten Point Coalition for their work in reducing violent crime and providing opportunities for young people. He commended the coalition for their success in reducing homicides by 85% in three communities and highlighted their inspiring work in the community. Pence also discussed the Trump administration's commitment to renewing opportunity and restoring public safety in cities, addressing the opioid addiction crisis, creating job opportunities, and reforming welfare programs. He emphasized the importance of education and providing access to a world-class education for every child. Pence concluded by encouraging the Ten Point Coalition to continue their important work and expressing his belief in the power of faith and community to bring about positive change.